Maruti Suzuki, Suzlon Energy, Tata Motors: India Stocks Preview

-- B y   A b h i s h e k   S h a n k e r
-- 
2011-09-13T23:34:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-13/maruti-suzuki-suzlon-energy-tata-motors-india-stocks-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in India trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the last close.  The BSE India Sensitive Index, or Sensex, lost 34.30
points, or 0.2 percent, to 16,467.44. The S&P CNX Nifty Index on
the National Stock Exchange slipped 0.1 percent to 4,940.95 and
the BSE 200 Index fell 0.1 to 2,042.38.  Maruti Suzuki India Ltd. (MSIL)  : The nation’s biggest
carmaker hired 100 new workers at its Manesar factory after
dismissing five employees who refused to sign a “good conduct
bond,” according to an e-mailed statement from the carmaker
yesterday. The shares rose 0.6 percent to 1,074.90 rupees.  Suzlon Energy Ltd. (SUEL)  : Repower Systems SE, a unit of
 Asia ’s third-largest turbine maker, is spending 10 million euros
($14 million) to expand two wind-turbine production facilities
in  Germany  to satisfy increasing demand, the company said on its
website. Suzlon Energy shares rose 0.1 percent to 39.20 rupees.  Tata Motors Ltd. (TTMT)  : Jaguar Land Rover is having
“intense discussions” with a Chinese automaker about a
potential partnership on manufacturing in the country, Chief
Executive Officer Ralf Speth said yesterday. The company is also
talking to other candidates, Speth said. The shares sank 4.6
percent to 139.60 rupees.  To contact the reporter on this story:
